description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Sadly Kennedy's father has passed away. No episodes for 11.09, 11.10, and 11.11.

Kennedy starts the night off thanking her audience for the well wishes. She recently lost her father and really appreciates it. Quickly she moves on to the FBN debate and its fallout. She was very pleased with the moderators at FBN - but of course she would be, she works at FBN. (I agree with her though. They were good moderators.) Snarky comments, interruptions, and a pushy Kasich. Then she moves on to the best part of the night. Rand Paul going after Marco Rubio. "How is it conservative to add a trillion dollars in military expenditures?" As expected there was more anti-immigrant rhetoric from Donald Trump. Apparently he's a big fan of Eisenhower's "Operation Wetback".

Trump is not backing down from his admiration of Eisenhower's mass deportation of immigrants. (Official called Operation Wetback.) ANTHONY CUMIA, BEN DOMENECH, and JOANNE NOSUCHINSKY are here to tell us what they think. Afterwards they move on to talking about Rand Paul's clash with Marco Rubio. Rand says Rubio isn't a real conservative for wanting to increase spending when we've already got an 18 trillion dollar debt. Rubio responds with this old chestnut, "You're isolationist!"

GREG GUTFELD is here to talk about the recent outbreak of PC madness taking over at Yale and Missouri. Free Speech, Halloween costumes, safe spaces, resignation, and Gutfeld's new book "I'm A Bouncy Boy."

Jeb Bush's campaign seems to be on the decline. PEGGY NOONAN is here to discuss. She talks her book, "The Time of Our Lives", Jeb Bush's campaign, and the chance he'll actually win the presidency.

Everyone is going after Carly Fiorina. Between the debate and Hillary cackling about a supporter choking her through the television she's had a hard couple weeks. Special guest COLIN QUINN joins the panel with ANTHONY CUMIA and JOANNE NOSUCHINSKY to discuss ... mostly Hillary. Afterwords they move onto Ben Carson's foreign policy missteps in the FBN debate.

Kennedy interviews COLIN QUINN one on one. He's starring in an off broadway play called "The New York Story". Directed by Jerry Sienfeld. They talk about his play, the university of Missouri, and political correctness.

The blue collar comic RON WHITE is here to talk about his run for the presidency. He's running as an independent. RON WHITE 2016.
